{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8746d62c-f55b-4dd4-9736-a9f012e28890","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Event flow:**\n\n| Transition | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created` → `Activated` |\n| User switches away | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` |\n| User returns | `Resumed` → `Activated` |\n| App closed | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` → `Destroying` |\n| iOS background snapshot | `Backgrounding` (save state via `e.State`) |\n\n> **Note:** `Backgrounding` is iOS-only and provides a state dictionary for saving session data before the OS may terminate the process.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ba514a94-0c70-4687-aa9b-036143f121ef","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development — I can answer it directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":440,"requestId":"3C38:16C73:D56BF7:1099904:6A0129BC"},"id":"43aa6ee1-59dd-48ae-a958-b0ffd62c51b9","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:58:44.332Z","parentId":"fcc17328-ff97-4aa4-b856-58d9cea8a6d1"}
